Case called at 10:37am [ma]
Defendant Collin Z Dohman in court with Attorney Karl E Huebner.  Theresa A Beck appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
The Court considers the warrant it issued earlier today satisfied by Mr. Dohman's appearance.

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST " entered; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

The Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, with conditions:

--to undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--maintain employment and/or education program; not to leave current employment unless another job lined up.
--not to be involved in any form of social media, to include chat rooms
--work towards obtaining license
--to pay statutory costs


Days credit for time already served:  10  days

The Court authorizes expungement upon successful completion of Probation, and successful completion of Probation term in Dane Co. case

The Court determines that Mr. Dohman has already provided a DNA sample

[MK] case called at 8:19am. 
Defendant Collin Z Dohman not in court. 
The notice for today's hearing was returned by the Postal Service with the handwritten notation: "Not Here" 
The Court issues a Bench Warrant for Mr. Dohman, to include a provision that Mr. Dohman may post $500 and be given a new court date and time, and then released. 
The Court $250 Cash Bond posted on 7/15/16 is found to be in default and the Court orders that to be forfeited.
recess 8:21am.
reconvene 8:32am. Defendant Collin Dohman now appears.
The Court quashes the Warrant, indicating that the Court considers the Warrant to have been executed since Mr. Dohman appears in court.
Mr. Dohman indicates that he has not made payments because he lost his job. 
The Court suspends the payment orders; the Court will address reimbursement of the attorney fee amount when the case is resolved.   However the Court instructs Mr. Dohman to resume making payments if he gains employment. 
The Court recinds the order that the posted $250 Cash Bond is forfeited.
After Mr. Dohman verifies that the N1642 Business 26, Fort Atkinson address is current, the Court instructs Mr. Dohman to speak with the owner of the residence to make sure that mailings are not returned, and if that is not workable, then Mr. Dohman will need to obtain a Post Office Box. 
recess 8:34am.
